The Royal Academy of Fine Arts (KASK) and the Royal Conservatoire together form the school of arts of HOGENT and Howest. The school brings talented and motivated students into contact with excellent pedagogues, active artists, designers and theorists of art and design. The development of the arts, education and research within an international perspective are its main tasks.

